Usage: writeFPlanScript [-help] [-appendToFile] [-compactRow]
                        -fileName <string> [-no_snap_to_grid] [-selected  | -sections {boundary row placeBlockages routeBlockages pinBlockages groups constraints pins ioPad areaIO bump partitions blocks globalNetConnect busSinkGroups blackboxes netGroupAndBusGuide relativefplan pinGroups pinGuides customShape coverCell pg_pins}]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-appendToFile                          # by default, we will create a new
                                       # output file(overwrite it if the file
                                       # already existed), this option will let
                                       # new data append to the file already
                                       # existed. (bool, optional)
-compactRow                            # Enable this command to write out the
                                       # row-creation commands in a simple and
                                       # compact way (bool, optional)
-fileName <string>                     # file name of dumped tcl command
                                       # (string, required)
-no_snap_to_grid                       # Specify object not snap to specified
                                       # grid. (bool, optional)
-sections {boundary row placeBlockages routeBlockages pinBlockages groups constraints pins ioPad areaIO bump partitions blocks globalNetConnect busSinkGroups blackboxes netGroupAndBusGuide relativefplan pinGroups pinGuides customShape coverCell pg_pins}
                                       # specify which kind of floorplan
                                       # objects need to be dumped out.
                                       # (enum_list, optional)
-selected                              # dump selected objects to file
                                       # (bool, optional)